OL,3,CMan jailed for sending threatening
OL,4,Cmessages to deputy first minister
OL,6,FAaron Thomas Curragh (34), from
OL,7,FWhincroft Road, was handed a 31-month
OL,8,Fsentence and he was told by Judge
OL,9,FGordon Kerr KC that he will spend half
OL,10,Fin custody and half on licence
OL,11,Ffollowing his release from prison.
OL,13,FCurragh had previously pleaded guilty
OL,14,Fto three charges of criminal damage
OL,15,Fand one of threatening communications.
OL,17,FThe first incident of criminal damage
OL,18,Foccurred in December 2023 at DUP MLA
OL,19,FJoanne Bunting's office on the Knock
OL,20,FRoad in the city. Several windows had
OL,21,Fbeen smashed.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/13
