OL,6,FMrs Little-Pengelly said the incident
OL,7,F"affected me deeply, made me feel
OL,8,Funcomfortable and I hated my own
OL,9,Fhouse''.
OL,11,FThe deputy first minister said that in
OL,12,Finitial period of months when the
OL,13,Fmessages were posted she "felt
OL,14,Fapprehensive and felt alone without my
OL,15,Fhusband there."
OL,17,FShe added: "I felt scared to come down
OL,18,Finto my house in the dark. I genuinely
OL,19,Ffelt like moving from my home and this
OL,20,Fis still the case today.''
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G8/13
