OL,6,FFollowing his guilty pleas, Curragh
OL,7,Fspoke to a probation officer and said
OL,8,Fthat after he got out of prison he
OL,9,Fplanned to leave Northern Ireland as
OL,10,Fit was "so bloody divided''.
OL,12,FThe probation officer noted Curragh
OL,13,Fpresented as paranoid claiming
OL,14,Ftelephone calls in the prison were
OL,15,Frecorded, and also noted were his
OL,16,Fexpressions of regret for his
OL,17,Fbehaviour but a lack of victim impact
OL,18,Fawareness.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G9/13
