OL,6,FDefence counsel Richard McConkey KC
OL,7,Fsaid it was felt Curragh needed a
OL,8,Fmental health assessment by either a
OL,9,Fpsychiatrist or a psychologist but the
OL,10,Fdefendant rejected this.
OL,12,FMr McConkey added that Curragh had
OL,13,Fsome "difficulties in his personal
OL,14,Flife in the previous nine years
OL,15,Fculminating in his offending
OL,16,Fbehaviour''.
OL,18,FJudge Kerr said: "This is a case which
OL,19,Finvolves, in my view, necessary
OL,20,Fdeterrent sentencing.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G10/13
