OL,6,F"It must be made clear that persons
OL,7,Fwho are elected representatives and by
OL,8,Fthe very nature of their jobs must
OL,9,Fmake themselves available to the
OL,10,Fpublic and provide facilities where
OL,11,Fthe public can go and get personal
OL,12,Fhelp and assistance when it is
OL,13,Frequired and that must be protected.
OL,15,F"It is more and more common these days
OL,16,Ffor public figures, including
OL,17,Fpoliticians, to be abused online.
OL,19,F"And that abuse, as proved in this
OL,20,Fcase, went well beyond any accepted
OL,21,Flevel of criticism.
